The approach presented in the paper is decentralized, which involves coordination and communication among multiple agents, making it relevant to the sub-category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA). The paper also deals with the problem of collision avoidance, which is a key issue in the design of robotic systems and falls under the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY). The approach presented in the paper involves planning trajectories for robots, which is a common problem in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents a time-complexity analysis of the proposed approach, which involves algorithmic design and analysis, making it relevant to the sub-category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
